  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\nWhen chat contains heavy messages and you open it after relogin or on the next day instead of spinner like in [Figma](https://www.figma.com/file/aS1ct66VQ6V0cio7vSqS8UoG/Chat?node-id=3%3A1031) you see \"It's been quiet here\"\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nSpinner like in [Figma](https://www.figma.com/file/aS1ct66VQ6V0cio7vSqS8UoG/Chat?node-id=3%3A1031) \r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n![rendering](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/69161550-a2043b00-0aeb-11ea-95bb-d7c8ff076772.gif)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Join to a chat with heavy messages (long text, markdown, ect)\r\n- Relogin\r\n- Open this chat again\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: nightly 19/11/2019\r\n- Operating System: Android, iOS (however messages are rendered faster on IOS, and this issue is not so visible)\r\n",
